    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00000015">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00000002"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>The main middle section of the insect body comprising three thoracic rings: the pro-, the meso- and the metathoraces which are more or less well fused and cask-like sometimes having on the upper lateral part one of two pairs of wings, while on the ventrolateral part each thoracic ring bears a pair of legs.</obo:IAO_0000115>
