        <obo:IAO_0000115>Cell that begins as a pole cell, becomes incorporated into the gonad and can develop into a germline stem cell (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997; Dansereau and Lasko, 2008; Slaidina et al., 2020).</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <oboInOwl:hasBroadSynonym>GC</oboInOwl:hasBroadSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>CL:0000301</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>PGC</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>fly_anatomy.ontology</oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>
        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>pole cell</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:id>FBbt:00000092</oboInOwl:id>
        <oboInOwl:inSubset rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/fbbt#FB_gloss"/>
        <oboInOwl:inSubset rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/fbbt#cur"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Can be identified in the larva by expression of vasa (Slaidina et al., 2020). Only a small subset of pole cells can become germ cells and this fate might be specified by the time the posterior midgut primordium invaginates (Okada, 1998).</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>primordial germ cell</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    <owl:Axiom>
        <owl:annotatedSource rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00000092"/>
        <owl:annotatedProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115"/>
        <owl:annotatedTarget>Cell that begins as a pole cell, becomes incorporated into the gonad and can develop into a germline stem cell (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997; Dansereau and Lasko, 2008; Slaidina et al., 2020).</owl:annotatedTarget>
