            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00000126"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002202"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005548"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002203"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00025999"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Anterior region of mesoderm that forms a vertical plate beside the anterior midgut rudiment (Campos Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). After its initial ingression during ventral furrow formation, it continues to recruit cells from the surface of the embryo until the end of stage 10 (Campos Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). It gives rise to the pharyngeal musculature, hemocytes, the corpus cardiacum and the visceral muscle of the esophagus (Campos Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997; de Velasco et al., 2006).</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>hms</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>procephalic mesoderm</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>fly_anatomy.ontology</oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>
        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>HeadMes</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>HeadMesP3</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>P4 HeadMes</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>head mesoderm P3 primordium</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>head mesoderm primordium P4</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:id>FBbt:00000127</oboInOwl:id>
        <oboInOwl:inSubset rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/fbbt#EmbDevSlim"/>
        <oboInOwl:inSubset rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/fbbt#cur"/>
        <rdfs:label>head mesoderm</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    <owl:Axiom>
        <owl:annotatedSource rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00000127"/>
        <owl:annotatedProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115"/>
        <owl:annotatedTarget>Anterior region of mesoderm that forms a vertical plate beside the anterior midgut rudiment (Campos Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). After its initial ingression during ventral furrow formation, it continues to recruit cells from the surface of the embryo until the end of stage 10 (Campos Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). It gives rise to the pharyngeal musculature, hemocytes, the corpus cardiacum and the visceral muscle of the esophagus (Campos Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997; de Velasco et al., 2006).</owl:annotatedTarget>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>FlyBase:FBrf0064803</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>FlyBase:FBrf0089570</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
