    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00000128 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00000128">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00004208"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005495"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00000102"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00000126"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002202"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005436"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002203"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00026000"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Region of mesoderm of that forms a layer interior to the ectoderm of the germ band (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). Following its invagination during ventral furrow formation in stages 6 and 7, it remains a coherent structure with no morphologically apparent subdivisions, apart from transient metamery during stage 9, until stage 11 (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). Its cells divide following invagination and it loses its epithelial integrity, forming a monolayer of cuboidal cells by stage 9 (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). A further division happens during stage 10 leading to two distinct layers by stage 11 (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>UBERON:6000128</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>mesoderm of the germ layer</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>fly_anatomy.ontology</oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>
        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>AtrunkMes</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>P2 TrMes</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>TrMes</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:id>FBbt:00000128</oboInOwl:id>
        <oboInOwl:inSubset rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/fbbt#EmbDevSlim"/>
        <oboInOwl:inSubset rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/fbbt#cur"/>
        <rdfs:label>trunk mesoderm</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    <owl:Axiom>
        <owl:annotatedSource rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00000128"/>
        <owl:annotatedProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115"/>
        <owl:annotatedTarget>Region of mesoderm of that forms a layer interior to the ectoderm of the germ band (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). Following its invagination during ventral furrow formation in stages 6 and 7, it remains a coherent structure with no morphologically apparent subdivisions, apart from transient metamery during stage 9, until stage 11 (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). Its cells divide following invagination and it loses its epithelial integrity, forming a monolayer of cuboidal cells by stage 9 (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). A further division happens during stage 10 leading to two distinct layers by stage 11 (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).</owl:annotatedTarget>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>FlyBase:FBrf0089570</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
    </owl:Axiom>
