                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00007114"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Glial cell with a nucleus amongst the neuronal cell bodies in the cell body rind. It is irregularly shaped, with processes that enclose the neuronal cell bodies.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>VFB:FBbt_00001297</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>CBG</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>cell body-associated glial cell</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>cortex associated CNS glial cell</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>cortex glial cell</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>fly_anatomy.ontology</oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>
        <oboInOwl:id>FBbt:00001297</oboInOwl:id>
        <oboInOwl:inSubset rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/fbbt#cur"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Glial cells associated with axonal tracts (such as those associated with nerve roots) are excluded from this class of glial cells (Ito et al., 1995). Modeled as &apos;part of&apos; their &apos;cell body rind&apos; regions, though in practice some cell body glia have small projections into the neuropil - https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1373-1705.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>cell body glial cell</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
