        <owl:annotatedTarget>Ring of imaginal tissue located at the anterior region of the embryonic/larval hindgut, posterior to where the Malpighian tubules join the hindgut, from which the adult hindgut forms. The hindgut imaginal ring cells are densely clustered, appear immature and have little cytoplasm (Murakami and Shiotsuki, 2001).</owl:annotatedTarget>
