    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00002618 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00002618">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00047362"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00001756"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002150"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00052537"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Nerve of larval abdominal segment 9 that has features of both the intersegmental and segmental nerves of more anterior segments (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). It has two roots and its proximal section is closely attached to the abdominal 8 nerve (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). After passing beneath the gut suspensor muscles, it gives off a thick recurrent branch, the hindgut nerve, which innervates the hindgut (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). Its main branch continues dorsoposteriorly and gives off a motor branch that innervates the A9 terminal oblique muscles (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). A posterior branch carries sensory axons from the anal sense organ and a dorsal branch carries axons of motor and sensory neurons of A9 (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>VFB:FBbt_00002618</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>nerve of a9</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>fly_anatomy.ontology</oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>
        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>larval abdominal 9 intersegmental nerve</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:id>FBbt:00002618</oboInOwl:id>
        <oboInOwl:inSubset rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/fbbt#cur"/>
        <rdfs:label>larval abdominal 9 nerve</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    <owl:Axiom>
        <owl:annotatedSource rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00002618"/>
        <owl:annotatedProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115"/>
        <owl:annotatedTarget>Nerve of larval abdominal segment 9 that has features of both the intersegmental and segmental nerves of more anterior segments (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). It has two roots and its proximal section is closely attached to the abdominal 8 nerve (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). After passing beneath the gut suspensor muscles, it gives off a thick recurrent branch, the hindgut nerve, which innervates the hindgut (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). Its main branch continues dorsoposteriorly and gives off a motor branch that innervates the A9 terminal oblique muscles (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). A posterior branch carries sensory axons from the anal sense organ and a dorsal branch carries axons of motor and sensory neurons of A9 (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).</owl:annotatedTarget>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>FlyBase:FBrf0089570</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
    </owl:Axiom>
    <owl:Axiom>
        <owl:annotatedSource rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00002618"/>
        <owl:annotatedProperty rdf:resource="http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasExactSynonym"/>
