            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005047"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002202"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005053"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002215"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0007585"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Specialized cell of the tracheal system that forms the secondary and terminal branches (tracheoles) of the tracheal tree. Each forms a secondary branch of a primary trachea. This secondary branch itself branches into multiple tracheoles within fine cytoplasmic projections that invade (tracheate) target tissues. Tracheolar cells are the main site of respiratory gaseous exchange within the tracheal system.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>tracheal end cell</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>tracheoblast</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>fly_anatomy.ontology</oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>
        <oboInOwl:id>FBbt:00005048</oboInOwl:id>
        <oboInOwl:inSubset rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/fbbt#cur"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Present at all developmental stages.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>tracheolar cell</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    <owl:Axiom>
        <owl:annotatedSource rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005048"/>
        <owl:annotatedProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115"/>
        <owl:annotatedTarget>Specialized cell of the tracheal system that forms the secondary and terminal branches (tracheoles) of the tracheal tree. Each forms a secondary branch of a primary trachea. This secondary branch itself branches into multiple tracheoles within fine cytoplasmic projections that invade (tracheate) target tissues. Tracheolar cells are the main site of respiratory gaseous exchange within the tracheal system.</owl:annotatedTarget>
