        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00025998"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>An immature hemocyte. It is highly basophilic, with a round to polygonal morphology and measures approximately 4 to 6 micrometers in diameter (Shrestha and Gateff, 1982). The nucleus is rich in nucleoli and is surrounded by a thin band of ribosome-rich cytoplasm (Shrestha and Gateff, 1982). In the larva, these cells can be found in the lymph gland primary lobe, or in circulation (Lanot et al., 2001).</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>CL:0000385</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>HSC</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Pr</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
