        <obo:IAO_0000115>Collective term for the masses and sheets of adipose tissue that are distributed throughout the organism&apos;s body. The adult and larval fat bodies are composed of different cell lineages, but perform the same main function of fat storage (Musselman and Kuhnlein, 2018).</obo:IAO_0000115>
