        <owl:annotatedTarget>Primordium of the late extended germ band and dorsal closure embryo that will give rise to the embryonic precursor of the adult muscle.</owl:annotatedTarget>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5948-3092</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
    </owl:Axiom>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005518 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005518">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00004208"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005495"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00006001"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005647"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002203"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00058297"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Primordium of the larval segmentally-repeated body wall musculature. It arises from the outer layer of the trunk mesoderm. During germ band shortening (stage 13), it segregates into loose segmental clusters. Within these clusters, muscle formation proceeds by fusion of fusion competent myoblasts to muscle founder cells. Formation of the embryonic/larval somatic musculature is complete by stage 17.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>fly_anatomy.ontology</oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>
        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>P1 SoMus</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>SoMusP2</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>somatic muscle specific anlage</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:id>FBbt:00005518</oboInOwl:id>
        <oboInOwl:inSubset rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/fbbt#EmbDevSlim"/>
        <oboInOwl:inSubset rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/fbbt#cur"/>
        <rdfs:label>somatic muscle primordium</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    <owl:Axiom>
        <owl:annotatedSource rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005518"/>
        <owl:annotatedProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115"/>
        <owl:annotatedTarget>Primordium of the larval segmentally-repeated body wall musculature. It arises from the outer layer of the trunk mesoderm. During germ band shortening (stage 13), it segregates into loose segmental clusters. Within these clusters, muscle formation proceeds by fusion of fusion competent myoblasts to muscle founder cells. Formation of the embryonic/larval somatic musculature is complete by stage 17.</owl:annotatedTarget>
