        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00004208"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005426"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00000128"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00004450"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Dorsal-most region of the trunk mesoderm that gives rise to the dorsal vessel (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). It forms a leading edge as the invaginated trunk mesoderm spreads from ventral to dorsal (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). The left and right regions eventually fuse at the dorsal midline and their cells differentiate into cardioblasts and pericardial cells (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <oboInOwl:hasAlternativeId>FBbt:00005561</oboInOwl:hasAlternativeId>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>CardMes</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>CardMesP2</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>P2 CardMes</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>cardiac mesoderm</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>mesodermal crest</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>fly_anatomy.ontology</oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>
        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>cardiac mesoderm primordium</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:id>FBbt:00005541</oboInOwl:id>
        <oboInOwl:inSubset rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/fbbt#EmbDevSlim"/>
        <oboInOwl:inSubset rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/fbbt#cur"/>
        <rdfs:label>cardiogenic mesoderm</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    <owl:Axiom>
        <owl:annotatedSource rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005541"/>
        <owl:annotatedProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115"/>
        <owl:annotatedTarget>Dorsal-most region of the trunk mesoderm that gives rise to the dorsal vessel (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). It forms a leading edge as the invaginated trunk mesoderm spreads from ventral to dorsal (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). The left and right regions eventually fuse at the dorsal midline and their cells differentiate into cardioblasts and pericardial cells (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).</owl:annotatedTarget>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>FlyBase:FBrf0089570</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>FlyBase:FBrf0253577</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
