            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Developing labial sensory organ that has not yet reached its mature larval state. It starts to become distinct, and the developing neurons form nerves, during stage 13 (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). As foregut structures move inwards, it becomes incorporated into the ventral part of atrium around stage 15 (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>fly_anatomy.ontology</oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>
        <oboInOwl:id>FBbt:00005619</oboInOwl:id>
