    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005786 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005786">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00007474"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005056"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002150"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005384"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Epithelial tube with excretory and osmoregulatory roles connected, via a ureter, to the alimentary canal at the junction of the hindgut and midgut. At mid-embryogenesis, there are 6 to 10 cells encircling the lumen, whereas later on, after a phase of tubule elongation, only 2 cells encircle the lumen. There are two pairs of Malpighian tubules: one pair arises from the dorsal part of the hindgut and lies at the anterior end of the abdomen; the other pair arises from the ventral part of the hindgut and lies at the posterior end of the abdomen. Each pair shares a common ureter. The anterior pair is longer than the posterior pair.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>UBERON:0001054</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>renal tubule</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>fly_anatomy.ontology</oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>
        <oboInOwl:id>FBbt:00005786</oboInOwl:id>
        <oboInOwl:inSubset rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/fbbt#FB_gloss"/>
        <oboInOwl:inSubset rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/fbbt#cur"/>
        <rdfs:label>Malpighian tubule</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    <owl:Axiom>
        <owl:annotatedSource rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005786"/>
        <owl:annotatedProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115"/>
        <owl:annotatedTarget>Epithelial tube with excretory and osmoregulatory roles connected, via a ureter, to the alimentary canal at the junction of the hindgut and midgut. At mid-embryogenesis, there are 6 to 10 cells encircling the lumen, whereas later on, after a phase of tubule elongation, only 2 cells encircle the lumen. There are two pairs of Malpighian tubules: one pair arises from the dorsal part of the hindgut and lies at the anterior end of the abdomen; the other pair arises from the ventral part of the hindgut and lies at the posterior end of the abdomen. Each pair shares a common ureter. The anterior pair is longer than the posterior pair.</owl:annotatedTarget>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>FlyBase:FBrf0030988</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>FlyBase:FBrf0160493</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>FlyBase:FBrf0166419</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
    </owl:Axiom>
    <owl:Axiom>
        <owl:annotatedSource rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005786"/>
