        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00007231"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Sensillum with an innervated external cuticular sensory structure consisting of one or more bipolar sensory neurons, and 3 support cells: a trichogen cell which makes the external cuticular sensory structure, a thecogen cell which makes the socket that holds the base of the external sensory structure and a tormogen cell which makes the cuticular matrix (cap) at the tip of the innervating dendrite(s).</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <terms:contributor rdf:resource="https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7073-9172"/>
        <terms:date rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2008-10-21T02:02:05Z</terms:date>
