    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00007295 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00007295">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00007316"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00001727"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002202"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00059198"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Group of sense organs, and the somas and dendrites of sensory neurons, located ventrally in a larval segment (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). It lies outside the ventrolateral and ventral muscles, beneath the ventral insertion of the lateral transverse muscles (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). It can be divided into two smaller clusters (ventral and ventral&apos;), with the axons of neurons of each cluster following a different branch of the segmental nerve (Willams and Shepherd, 1999). The pattern of sense organs and neurons is highly similar in segments A1-7, and slightly modified in the thoracic segments (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <terms:contributor rdf:resource="https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7073-9172"/>
        <terms:date rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2008-11-18T01:31:32Z</terms:date>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>ventral group of sensory organs</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>fly_anatomy.ontology</oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>
        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>embryonic/larval thoracic/abdominal ventral sensory cluster</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>larval thoracic/abdominal ventral sensory cluster</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:id>FBbt:00007295</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:comment>Terminal (A8-10) segments have substantially different morphology, such that no &apos;ventral cluster&apos; is present as seen in more anterior segments.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>larval ventral sensory cluster group</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    <owl:Axiom>
        <owl:annotatedSource rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00007295"/>
        <owl:annotatedProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115"/>
        <owl:annotatedTarget>Group of sense organs, and the somas and dendrites of sensory neurons, located ventrally in a larval segment (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). It lies outside the ventrolateral and ventral muscles, beneath the ventral insertion of the lateral transverse muscles (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). It can be divided into two smaller clusters (ventral and ventral&apos;), with the axons of neurons of each cluster following a different branch of the segmental nerve (Willams and Shepherd, 1999). The pattern of sense organs and neurons is highly similar in segments A1-7, and slightly modified in the thoracic segments (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).</owl:annotatedTarget>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>FlyBase:FBrf0089570</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>FlyBase:FBrf0108300</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>FlyBase:FBrf0183734</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
    </owl:Axiom>
