        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>aimpr</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>anterior inferior medial protocerebrum</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>anterior inferior protocerebrum</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:id>FBbt:00045037</oboInOwl:id>
        <oboInOwl:inSubset rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/fbbt#BrainName"/>
        <rdfs:comment>The name crepine is used in French cuisine to refer to a slice of meat wrapped around some delicacy. The posterior region of the crepine corresponds to the dorsal part of the inferior dorsofrontal protocerebrum (IDFP) of Chiang et al. (2011) (Ito et al., 2014).</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>adult crepine</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
