        <oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>fly_anatomy.ontology</oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>
        <oboInOwl:id>FBbt:00047891</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:comment>Hartenstein et al. (2018) say this (and not other mandibular/maxillary commissures) can be distinguished at later stages of development, and also show only one (intermediate) anterior commissure in the maxillary neuromere, so this is probably the intermediate anterior subesophageal (ISA) commissure of Kuert et al. (2014) - https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1373-1705.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>maxillary anterior commissure</rdfs:label>
