        <obo:IAO_0000115>Cluster of cells in the ventrolateral ectoderm in the embryonic thorax that will eventually give rise to a dorsal imaginal disc, a ventral (leg) imaginal disc and a Keilin organ in the larva. The three different cellular identities cannot be distinguished at stage 11, but can by stage 14. There is one per thoracic hemisegment (six total).</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <terms:contributor rdf:resource="https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1373-1705"/>
        <terms:date rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2019-08-23T09:38:06Z</terms:date>
