        <owl:annotatedTarget>Cluster of cells in the ventrolateral ectoderm in the embryonic thorax that will eventually give rise to a dorsal imaginal disc, a ventral (leg) imaginal disc and a Keilin organ in the larva. The three different cellular identities cannot be distinguished at stage 11, but can by stage 14. There is one per thoracic hemisegment (six total).</owl:annotatedTarget>
