    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00049277 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00049277">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00001722"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00001715"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>A closely associated cluster of three neuroendocrine glands of the late embryo or larva, located anterior to the brain and dorsal to the esophagus (de Velasco et al., 2004). It consists of the corpus cardiacum posteroventrally (closest to the brain), the prothoracic gland laterally (forming most of the ring gland) and the corpus allatum anterodorsally (furthest from the brain) (de Velasco et al., 2004). It is innervated by neurons of the nerve of the corpus cardiacum and the aorta passes through it (de Velasco et al., 2004).</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <terms:contributor rdf:resource="https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1373-1705"/>
        <terms:date rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2021-02-08T14:06:45Z</terms:date>
        <oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>fly_anatomy.ontology</oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>
        <oboInOwl:id>FBbt:00049277</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:label>larval ring gland</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    <owl:Axiom>
        <owl:annotatedSource rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00049277"/>
        <owl:annotatedProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115"/>
        <owl:annotatedTarget>A closely associated cluster of three neuroendocrine glands of the late embryo or larva, located anterior to the brain and dorsal to the esophagus (de Velasco et al., 2004). It consists of the corpus cardiacum posteroventrally (closest to the brain), the prothoracic gland laterally (forming most of the ring gland) and the corpus allatum anterodorsally (furthest from the brain) (de Velasco et al., 2004). It is innervated by neurons of the nerve of the corpus cardiacum and the aorta passes through it (de Velasco et al., 2004).</owl:annotatedTarget>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>FlyBase:FBrf0064803</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>FlyBase:FBrf0179777</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>FlyBase:FBrf0194938</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>FlyBase:FBrf0239029</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
    </owl:Axiom>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00049278 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00049278">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00001722"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00003214"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Cluster consisting of the corpus allatum (CA), corpus cardiacum (CC) and hypocerebral ganglion of the adult (Hartenstein, 1993). During pupal stages, the ring gland migrates posteriorly to its adult position, just anterior to the proventriculus (cardia), the prothoracic gland degenerates and the corpus cardiacum becomes fused to the hypocerebral ganglion (Dai and Gilbert, 1991; Nassel and Zandawala, 2020).</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <terms:contributor rdf:resource="https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1373-1705"/>
        <terms:date rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2021-02-08T14:05:50Z</terms:date>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>ring gland of the adult</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>fly_anatomy.ontology</oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>
        <oboInOwl:id>FBbt:00049278</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:label>adult ring gland</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    <owl:Axiom>
        <owl:annotatedSource rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00049278"/>
        <owl:annotatedProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115"/>
        <owl:annotatedTarget>Cluster consisting of the corpus allatum (CA), corpus cardiacum (CC) and hypocerebral ganglion of the adult (Hartenstein, 1993). During pupal stages, the ring gland migrates posteriorly to its adult position, just anterior to the proventriculus (cardia), the prothoracic gland degenerates and the corpus cardiacum becomes fused to the hypocerebral ganglion (Dai and Gilbert, 1991; Nassel and Zandawala, 2020).</owl:annotatedTarget>
