            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Neuroblast that has serial homologues across multiple neuromeres. All neuroblasts of the ventral nerve cord and gnathal ganglia are segmentally-repeated (Urbach et al., 2016). Most neuroblasts of the tritocerebrum and some neuroblasts of the deutocerebrum also have serial homology to neuroblasts of more posterior segments (Urbach et al., 2016).</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <terms:contributor rdf:resource="https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1373-1705"/>
        <terms:date rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2021-06-10T15:10:07Z</terms:date>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>VFB:FBbt_00051362</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>serially-homologous neuroblast</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>fly_anatomy.ontology</oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>
        <oboInOwl:id>FBbt:00051362</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:comment>Applies to neuroblasts at all stages of development.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>segmentally-repeated neuroblast</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    <owl:Axiom>
        <owl:annotatedSource rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00051362"/>
        <owl:annotatedProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115"/>
        <owl:annotatedTarget>Neuroblast that has serial homologues across multiple neuromeres. All neuroblasts of the ventral nerve cord and gnathal ganglia are segmentally-repeated (Urbach et al., 2016). Most neuroblasts of the tritocerebrum and some neuroblasts of the deutocerebrum also have serial homology to neuroblasts of more posterior segments (Urbach et al., 2016).</owl:annotatedTarget>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>FlyBase:FBrf0232096</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
    </owl:Axiom>
